  "156": "CLASS: ENGINEERING GROUP: NERO'S CREW FACTION: ROMULAN STAR EMPIRE Nero is a Romulan mining ship Captain who comes from an alternate future. In his timeline's 2387, Nero witnessed the destruction of his homeworld of Romulus. The untimely efforts of Ambassador Spock to contain the supernova that engulfed his planet resulted in the creation of an artificial black hole, which created this offshoot reality. On arrival, Nero's vessel, the Narada, was heavily damaged in combat with the USS Kelvin, leaving Nero and his crew stranded. Nero lost his family when the disaster occurred and on that day, promised himself retribution against Spock for his failure.",
  "157": "Nero",
  "158": "NERO",
  "159": "See the Flaws Every time the ship strikes the opponent with a weapon attack, Nero has a {0:0.#%} chance of Burning it for two rounds. Officer Abilities are activated when assigned to the bridge of a ship.",
  "160": "See the Flaws",
  "161": "{1:#,#%} chance to cause Burning to the enemy when hitting it",
  "162": "Joy In Vengeance At the beginning of each round, if the opponent's ship is Burning, Nero increases the Damage of the weapons by {0:0.#%}. Captain Maneuvers are activated when an officer is captain of a ship.",
  "163": "Joy In Vengeance",
  "164": "+{0:#,#%} to Damage when the enemy ship is Burning",
  "165": "Romulan Tenacity The ship can resurrect with {0:#,#%} of its Hull Health. This takes precedence over the NSEA Protector’s Omega-13 Ship Ability and does not stack. Feel the Heat {2:#,#%} of the Health of Officers deducted from the Shield Health of a Burning Ship",
  "166": "Romulan Tenacity The ship can resurrect with {0:#,#%} of its Hull Health. Does not stack with the NSEA Protector's Omega-13 ability. Feel the Heat {2:#,#%} of the Health of Officers deducted from the Shield Health of a Burning Ship",
  "167": "CLASS: SCIENCE GROUP: NERO'S CREW FACTION: ROMULAN STAR EMPIRE Vemet worked on the Narada for years; a friend of Nero's and a constant voice of caution and reason, Vemet helped steer the crew through many a difficult situation. When Nero called for revenge, Vemet advised care and planning, but provided his service all the same.",
  "168": "Vemet",
  "169": "VEMET",
  "170": "Feel the Heat At the beginning of each round, if the opponent's ship is Burning, Vemet decreases its Shield Health by an amount equal to {0:0.#%} of the Health of all Officers on the ship. Officer Abilities are activated when assigned to the bridge of a ship.",
  "171": "Feel the Heat",
  "172": "{0:#,#%} of total Officer Health deducted from the Shield Health of a Burning ship each round",
  "173": "Romulan Tenacity If the ship survives an attack that depletes its shields and is destroyed in one of the following attacks during the same battle, the battle is lost but Vemet heals {0:0.#%} of the Hull Health and the ship survives. This takes precedence over the NSEA Protector’s Omega-13 Ship Ability and does not stack. Captain Maneuvers are activated when an officer is captain of a ship.",
  "174": "Romulan Tenacity",
  "175": "The ship can resurrect with {0:#,#%} of the ship's hull health. This takes precedence over the NSEA Protector’s Omega-13 Ship Ability and does not stack.",
  "176": "Discipline +{0:#,#%} to all Officer Stats each round Watch the World burn +{2:#,#%} To Armor, Shield Deflection and Dodge when the opponent is Burning",
  "177": "Discipline +{0:#,#%} to all Officer Stats each round Watch the World burn +{2:#,#%} To Armor, Shield Deflection and Dodge when the opponent is Burning",
  "178": "CLASS: COMMAND GROUP: NERO'S CREW FACTION: ROMULAN STAR EMPIRE Kumak was the tactical officer aboard the Narada. Before the destruction of Romulus, Kumak was an expert with a mining laser, able to bore impressively precise seams into asteroids. That skill transferred over surprisingly well to shooting down Federation starships.",
  "179": "Kumak",
  "180": "KUMAK",
