  "783": "Endless Ambition +{0:#,#%} to the Captain's Stats Fatal Charm {3:#,#%} chance to increase damage by 300% of Officers Attack",
  "784": "Endless Ambition +{0:#,#%} to the Captain's Stats Fatal Charm {3:#,#%} chance to increase damage by 300% of Officers Attack",
  "785": "CLASS: COMMAND GROUP: OUTLAWS FACTION: NONE Harry Mudd’s half-Human, half-Bajoran daughter, she grew a deep resentment towards her father after being abandoned by him at an early age. However, she couldn’t resist following in his footsteps, becoming one of the most notorious thieves and smugglers in the galaxy. With her eventual goal to take over her father’s operations, Ro is driven by ambition, rather than the ego and cynicism that drives Harry, and wants to build a sustainable empire beyond her father’s schemes and vanity projects.",
  "786": "Ro Mudd",
  "787": "RO MUDD",
  "788": "Fatal Charm At the start of combat, Ro Mudd has a {0:0.#%} chance of increasing the Damage dealt by the ship by 300% of the total Attack of all officers on the ship for the whole combat. Officer Abilities are activated when assigned to the bridge of a ship.",
  "789": "Fatal Charm",
  "790": "{1:#,#%} chance to increase damage by 300% of Officers Attack",
  "791": "Endless Ambition Ro Mudd increases her stats by {0:#.#%} when she is the captain. Captain Maneuvers are activated when an officer is captain of a ship.",
  "792": "Endless Ambition",
  "793": "+{0:#,#%} to the Captain's Stats",
  "794": "Grizzled Veteran +{0:#,#%} to Critical Hit Chance against hostiles for the first round Military Training +{2:#,#%} to Ship XP gained while fighting",
  "795": "Grizzled Veteran +{0:#,#%} to Critical Hit Chance against hostiles for the first round Military Training +{2:#,#%} to Ship XP gained while fighting",
  "796": "CLASS: SCIENCE GROUP: OUTLAWS FACTION: NONE A former Starfleet MACO veteran, Goon has seen his fair share of battles, the memories of which have stuck with him. Becoming disillusioned by Starfleet’s perceived hypocrisy – in particular, the actions displayed by Kirk and his ilk – Goon left Starfleet to use his considerable talents and arsenal elsewhere, now acting as Mudd’s weapons expert. Always willing to give you a blunt and honest opinion, occasionally to his detriment, he’s also the first person Mudd will call if he ever finds himself outgunned.",
  "797": "Goon",
  "798": "GOON",
  "799": "Military Training Goon increases the Ship XP gained by the ship from fighting by {0:0.#%}. Officer Abilities are activated when assigned to the bridge of a ship.",
  "800": "Military Training",
  "801": "+{0:#,#%} to Ship XP gained while fighting",
  "802": "Grizzled Veteran When fighting Hostiles, Goon increases the chances of dealing a Critical Hit by {0:#.#%} for the first round of combat. Captain Maneuvers are activated when an officer is captain of a ship.",
  "803": "Grizzled Veteran",
  "804": "+{0:#,#%} to Critical Hit Chance against hostiles for the first round",
  "805": "Chirurgical Precision +{0:#,#%} to Critical Hit Chance for the first three rounds against Eclipse hostiles. Shield Remodulation {3:#,#%} chance to reduce Eclipse hostiles's mitigation by 40%",
  "806": "Chirurgical Precision +{0:#,#%} to Critical Hit Chance for the first three rounds against Eclipse hostiles. Shield Remodulation {3:#,#%} chance to reduce Eclipse hostiles's mitigation by 40%",
  "807": "CLASS: ENGINEERING GROUP: OUTLAWS FACTION: NONE Ahvix is a visitor to our galaxy, albeit an unwilling one. After an incident with her ship, Ahvix found herself stranded here, in the company of Mudd and his crew of Rogues. At first, they were unsure of this unknown alien but Ahvix quickly proved herself as a reliable and skilled officer and became an invaluable asset to the crew. While she still searches for a way home to this day, Ahvix has found something most unexpected in this strange, new galaxy... Friends.",
  "808": "Ahvix",
  "809": "AHVIX",
  "810": "Shield Remodulation When fighting Eclipse hostiles (including Armadas), Ahvix has a {0:0.#%} chance to decrease the Shield Deflection, Armor and Dodge of the opponent by 40% . Officer Abilities are activated when assigned to the bridge of a ship.",
  "811": "Shield Remodulation",
  "812": "{1:#,#%} chance to reduce Eclipse hostiles's mitigation by 40%",
  "813": "Chirurgical Precision When fighting Eclipse hostiles (including Armada Targets), for the first three rounds of combat, Ahvix increases the chances of a Critical Hit by {0:0.#%} Captain Maneuvers are activated when an officer is captain of a ship.",
  "814": "Chirurgical Precision",
  "815": "+{0:#,#%} to Critical Hit Chance for the first three rounds against Eclipse hostiles.",
  "816": "Security Breach -{0:#,#%} to Eclipse hostile's Shield Mitigation for the first three rounds Mirani Technology {3:#,#%} chance to increase mitigation by 100% against Eclipse hostiles",
  "817": "Security Breach -{0:#,#%} to Eclipse hostile's Shield Mitigation for the first three rounds Mirani Technology {3:#,#%} chance to increase mitigation by 100% against Eclipse hostiles",
  "818": "CLASS: COMMAND GROUP: OUTLAWS FACTION: NONE One of the last of the Mirani alien race, Tiza and the other Mirani were forced out of their territory a century ago by Eclipse, who took over that area to create the Exchange. A handful of survivors managed to escape, building new lives for themselves on previously deserted planets. While most records of the Mirani have since been wiped out by Eclipse, they were known as technological pioneers in their prime, and that talent has been passed on to the new generation of Mirani, including Tiza. Now, as the leader of the remaining Mirani, Tiza believes it’s time to take back their systems from Eclipse.",
  "819": "Tiza",
  "820": "TIZA",
  "821": "Mirani Technology When fighting Eclipse hostiles (including Armadas), Tiza has a {0:0.#%} chance to increase Shield Deflection, Armor and Dodge by 100% for the whole combat. Officer Abilities are activated when assigned to the bridge of a ship.",
  "822": "Mirani Technology",
  "823": "{1:#,#%} chance to increase mitigation by 100% against Eclipse hostiles",
  "824": "Security Breach When fighting Eclipse hostiles (including Armada Targets), for the first three rounds of combat, Tiza decreases the Shield Mitigation of the opponent by {0:0.#%} Captain Maneuvers are activated when an officer is captain of a ship.",
  "825": "Security Breach",
  "826": "-{0:#,#%} to Eclipse hostile's Shield Mitigation for the first round",
  "827": "Two steps ahead {1:#,#%} chance to have 98% shield mitigation for the first two rounds of combat 823 ways to die {3:#,#%} chance to double shots for the first round",
  "828": "Two steps ahead {1:#,#%} chance to have 98% shield mitigation for the first two rounds of combat 823 ways to die {3:#,#%} chance to double shots for the first round",
  "829": "CLASS: SCIENCE GROUP: OUTLAWS FACTION: NONE Harcourt Fenton Mudd. Many call him a thief, a liar, a rogue, a con-man. He is all of these things. But he is, above all, a survivor. Arriving in our universe through a complicated series of mycellial networks, this alternate Mudd might, at first, seem similar to our own. Indeed, he is charming, quick witted and incredibly intelligent but this Mudd has one crucial differentiating factor. There is no line he will not cross. The cruel fate he suffered at the hands of Klingon captors hardened Mudd, turning him ruthless. It showed him that there can be no room for morals in the fight for survival. This new outlook, as well as his penchant for cons and thievery, put him at odds with the crew of the USS Discovery, who have proven to be a mighty thorn in his side. Now that Mudd is here, he will do whatever it takes to make it out alive… and maybe wreak a little havoc while he’s at it.",
  "830": "Harcourt Fenton Mudd",
  "831": "HARRY MUDD",
