  "904": "Art of War -{0:#,#%} to opponent's Captain's Maneuver effectiveness Know your Enemy -{2:#,#%} To all the stats of the opponent's Bridge Officers",
  "905": "Art of War -{0:#,#%} to opponent's Captain's Maneuver effectiveness Know your Enemy -{2:#,#%} To all the stats of the opponent's Bridge Officers",
  "906": "CLASS: SCIENCE GROUP: GLORY IN THE KILL FACTION: KLINGON EMPIRE Kras has served in advisory roles for some time now; more a scientist and negotiator than a commander, but a warrior all the same. Behind many of the rising stars in the Klingon forces, Kras has quietly imparted knowledge and experience. Koloth, Kor, and Kang all count Kras as mentor in their early career. Recently, Kras has turned his attention to Klaa and his crew.",
  "907": "Kras",
  "908": "KRAS",
  "909": "Know your Enemy Kras decreases the Attack, Defense and Health of all the Officers on the Bridge of the opponent's ship by {0:0.#%}. Officer Abilities are activated when assigned to the bridge of a ship.",
  "910": "Know your Enemy",
  "911": "-{0:#,#%} To all the stats of the opponent's Bridge Officers",
  "912": "Art of War Kras decreases the effectiveness of the opponent's Captain's Maneuver by {0:0.#%}. Captain Maneuvers are activated when an officer is captain of a ship.",
  "913": "Art of War",
  "914": "-{0:#,#%} to opponent's Captain's Maneuver effectiveness",
  "915": "Hot Pursuit +{0:#,#%} to Impulse Speed Critical Strike +{2:#,#%} to Critical Hit Damage",
  "916": "Hot Pursuit +{0:#,#%} to Impulse Speed Critical Strike +{2:#,#%} to Critical Hit Damage",
  "917": "CLASS: COMMAND GROUP: GLORY IN THE KILL FACTION: KLINGON EMPIRE Klaa is a young and impetuous lieutenant in the Klingon Defense Force; his eagerness to prove his prowess and honor in battle has led him into some tricky tactical situations. Thus far, Kras's advice, Klaa's loyal crew, and Klaa's ferocity have earned only victories. This has only fed Klaa's ambition.",
  "918": "Klaa",
  "919": "KLAA",
  "920": "Critical Strike Klaa increases the Critical Hit Damage of the ship by {0:0.#%}. Officer Abilities are activated when assigned to the bridge of a ship.",
  "921": "Critical Strike",
  "922": "+{0:#,#%} to Critical Hit Damage",
  "923": "Hot Pursuit Klaa increases the Impulse Speed of the ship by {0:0.#%}. Captain Maneuvers are activated when an officer is captain of a ship.",
  "924": "Hot Pursuit",
  "925": "+{0:#,#%} to Impulse Speed",
  "926": "Fake Communiques {1:#,#%} chance to delay opponent's Weapons each round for 1 round Energy Absorption -{2:#,#%} less Energy Damage from player enemies",
  "927": "Fake Communiques {1:#,#%} chance to delay opponent's Weapons each round for 1 round Energy Absorption -{2:#,#%} less Energy Damage from player enemies",
  "928": "CLASS: SCIENCE GROUP: GLORY IN THE KILL FACTION: KLINGON EMPIRE Vixis is foremost among Klaa's warriors, and mans the targeting scanners. Her impressive muscles have earned her plenty of compliments and suitors, but she has no interest in the trivialities of the bedroom; her focus is on battle and glory, as any true warrior's should be.",
  "929": "Vixis",
  "930": "VIXIS",
  "931": "Energy Absorption Vixis decreases the Energy Weapon Damage of opponent players by {0:0.#%}. Officer Abilities are activated when assigned to the bridge of a ship.",
  "932": "Energy Absorption",
  "933": "-{0:#,#%} less Energy Damage from player enemies",
  "934": "Fake Communiques At the beginning of each round, Vixis has a {0:#.#%} chance of delaying the opponent Weapon Fire by one round. Captain Maneuvers are activated when an officer is captain of a ship.",
  "935": "Fake Communiques",
  "936": "{0:#,#%} chance to delay opponent's Weapons each round for 1 round",
  "937": "Battleship Specialist +{0:#,#%} to Weapon Damage of Battleships against players Resist Kinetic -{2:#,#%} to Kinetic Weapon Damage from enemy player's ships",
  "938": "Battleship Specialist +{0:#,#%} to Weapon Damage of Battleships against players Resist Kinetic -{2:#,#%} to Kinetic Weapon Damage from enemy player's ships",
  "939": "CLASS: ENGINEERING GROUP: GLORY IN THE KILL FACTION: KLINGON EMPIRE Komal is unusual among Klingons in that he actually prefers to be an engineer. He puts up a proper front when around his fellows, but in his heart of hearts, he'd rather be wrenching than fighting. He's found success on Klaa's crew, as Klaa's competitive nature and Kras's measured attitude have worked in tandem to allow Komal to spend his efforts on engineering.",
  "940": "Komal",
  "941": "KOMAL",
