  "1154": "Tribble Mining Collective",
  "1155": "+{0:#,#%} to Mining Speed",
  "1156": "Multiplicative Extraction Ten of Eleven increases the speed of Parsteel, Tritanium and Dilithium Mining by {0:0.#%}. Captain Maneuvers are activated when an officer is captain of a ship.",
  "1157": "Multiplicative Extraction",
  "1158": "+{0:#,#%} to Parsteel, Tritanium and Dilithium Mining Speed",
  "1159": "Vulcan Hello +{0:#} to all Officer Attack Risk-Taker +{2:#,#%} to Damage",
  "1160": "Vulcan Hello +{0:#} to all Officer Attack Risk-Taker +{2:#,#%} to Damage",
  "1161": "CLASS: COMMAND GROUP: DISCOVERY FACTION: FEDERATION A true prodigy, Commander Michael Burnham was raised by Ambassador Sarek on the Vulcan homeworld. She was intended to act as a bridge between Vulcan and human societies, a living testament to the potential of both species. Unfortunately, anti-human bias among the elite prevented Michael from ascending as far as she deserved. Crestfallen, Michael elected instead to enlist in Starfleet, where she was put under the command of one Captain Phillipa Georgiou, of the USS Shenzhou. Burnham and Georgiou formed a strong bond, and Michael eventually earned a place at Captain Georgiou's right hand, as her first officer.",
  "1162": "Origins Burnham",
  "1163": "ORIGINS BURNHAM",
  "1164": "Risk-Taker Origins Burnham increases the Weapon Damage of the ship by {0:0.#%}. Officer Abilities are activated when assigned to the bridge of a ship.",
  "1165": "Risk-Taker",
  "1166": "+{0:#,#%} to Damage",
  "1167": "Vulcan Hello Origins Burnham increases the Attack of all the Officers on the ship by {0:#}. Captain Maneuvers are activated when an officer is captain of a ship.",
  "1168": "Vulcan Hello",
  "1169": "+{0:#} to all Officer Attack",
  "1170": "Vigilant +{0:#} to all Officer Defense Prey Instinct +{2:#,#%} to Hull Health",
  "1171": "Vigilant +{0:#} to all Officer Defense Prey Instinct +{2:#,#%} to Hull Health",
  "1172": "CLASS: SCIENCE GROUP: DISCOVERY FACTION: FEDERATION Lieutenant Saru was born to a life of constant fear. His people, the Kelpiens, are a prey species on their home planet of Kaminar. No strangers to death, the Kelpiens have evolved to sense the presence of danger, a trait which has brought Saru no shortage of success... and pain. Saru did not share his people's apathy toward their place in the ecosystem. He resented being prey and sought to find a way out. Utilizing some broken alien technology, he managed to send a message out to the void, hoping that someone would hear it. Someone did. Captain Philippa Georgiou of the USS Shenzhou was impressed by Saru's ingenuity and his bravery. So impressed that she broke several Starfleet laws and offered him a place on her crew. Saru has spent the years since tirelessly working to earn the respect of his peers. He has risen through the ranks of Starfleet and was even assigned to the Shenzhou bridge as its Science Officer.",
  "1173": "Origins Saru",
  "1174": "ORIGINS SARU",
  "1175": "Prey Instinct Origins Saru increases the Hull Health of the ship by {0:0.#%}. Officer Abilities are activated when assigned to the bridge of a ship.",
  "1176": "Prey Instinct",
  "1177": "+{0:#,#%} to Hull Health",
  "1178": "Vigilant Origins Saru increases the Defense of all the Officers on the ship by {0:#}. Captain Maneuvers are activated when an officer is captain of a ship.",
  "1179": "Vigilant",
  "1180": "+{0:#} to all Officer Defense",
  "1181": "Biologist +{0:#} to all Officer Health No Time To Waste +{2:#,#%} to Warp Speed",
  "1182": "Biologist +{0:#} to all Officer Health No Time To Waste +{2:#,#%} to Warp Speed",
  "1183": "CLASS: ENGINEERING GROUP: DISCOVERY FACTION: FEDERATION When one thinks of a 'genius', they probably imagine someone very much like Paul Stamets. Trained as an astromycologist, Stamets sought to shatter conventional thinking around biology and physics. In fact, he did not believe in the concept of biology and physics as separate sciences. He believed in biology as physics. He believed that to truly advance humanity, one needed to transcend traditional wisdom and expand the borders of scientific discovery. To that end, he and his research partner Straal began work on a project - A new technology that would change the galaxy as we know it. Combining astrobiology with astroengineering, they set out to create a new method of space travel, one that would utilize a renewable fuel source to send ships farther than they ever could before, at speeds no-one thought possible. Unfortunately, several setbacks would prevent them from reaching their full potential. However, no matter what stands in his way, no matter how many obstacles he needs to surmount, Paul Stamets will never give up on his ultimate goal... To revolutionize scientific exploration and change the galaxy for the better.",
  "1184": "Origins Stamets",
  "1185": "ORIGINS STAMETS",
  "1186": "No Time To Waste Origins Stamets increases the Warp Speed of the ship by {0:0.#%}. Officer Abilities are activated when assigned to the bridge of a ship.",
  "1187": "No Time To Waste",
  "1188": "+{0:#,#%} to Warp Speed",
  "1189": "Biologist Origins Stamets increases the Health of all the Officers on the ship by {0:#}. Captain Maneuvers are activated when an officer is captain of a ship.",
  "1190": "Biologist",
  "1191": "+{0:#} to all Officer Health",
  "1192": "Steadfast +{0:#} to Impulse Speed Intuitive {2:0.#%} of Attack removed from opponent's SHP",
  "1193": "Steadfast +{0:#} to Impulse Speed Intuitive {2:0.#%} of Attack removed from opponent's SHP",
  "1194": "CLASS: SCIENCE GROUP: DISCOVERY CREW FACTION: FEDERATION Once meant to stand as the living embodiment of Human and Vulcan potential, Michael Burnham’s life took a disastrous turn after the Battle at the Binary Stars. Branded a mutineer and sentenced to imprisonment for life, she had given up all hope of living up to her incredible potential. However, the war was not finished and Burnham still had a part to play. She was brought aboard the USS Discovery to serve under Captain Gabriel Lorca. She would pay off her debt to society by helping him win the war against the Klingons. Lorca gave her the greatest gift she ever could have received... Something to fight for. Michael has come to see the Discovery’s crew as her own family and will stop at nothing to defend them.",
  "1195": "Michael Burnham",
  "1196": "MICHAEL BURNHAM",
  "1197": "Intuitive When fighting players, for each weapon attack that hits the opponent, Michael Burnham removes {0:0.#%} of the total Attack of all Officers on your Ship from the opponent's Shield Health. (Weapons with multiple shots will only trigger this ability once per attack.) Officer Abilities are activated when assigned to the bridge of a ship.",
  "1198": "Intuitive",
  "1199": "{0:0.#%} of Attack removed from opponent's SHP",
