  "1201": "Steadfast",
  "1202": "+{0:#} to Impulse Speed",
  "1203": "Precautions -{0:0.#%} to opponent's Critical Hit Chance when receiving a Critical Hit. Avoid Danger -{2:0.#%} to opponent's weapon damage",
  "1204": "Precautions -{0:0.#%} to opponent's Critical Hit Chance when receiving a Critical Hit. Avoid Danger -{2:0.#%} to opponent's weapon damage",
  "1205": "CLASS: COMMAND GROUP: DISCOVERY CREW FACTION: FEDERATION Commander Saru knows better than anyone what it is to feel fear. He lived his life on Kaminar constantly afraid, waiting for death to come, but it never did. Instead, he used his ingenuity to escape and forged a new life in Starfleet. Ever since the Battle at the Binary Stars, Saru has continued to excel, proving to all who encounter him that he represents the best Starfleet has to offer. He is compassionate, wise, measured and cautious. All elements of a great Starfleet officer. Though his evolutionary tendency toward fear may hold him back at times, Saru has proven time and again that he will not let anything stop him from achieving his goals or protecting those closest to him.",
  "1206": "Saru",
  "1207": "SARU",
  "1208": "Avoid Danger When fighting players, Saru decreases the opponent's weapon damage by {0:0.#%}. Officer Abilities are activated when assigned to the bridge of a ship.",
  "1209": "Avoid Danger",
  "1210": "-{0:0.#%} to opponent's weapon damage",
  "1211": "Precautions When fighting players, every time your ship is hit by a Critical Hit, Saru decreases the Critical Hit Chance of the opponent's ship by {0:0.#%}. Captain Maneuvers are activated when an officer is captain of a ship.",
  "1212": "Precautions",
  "1213": "-{0:0.#%} to opponent's Critical Hit Chance when receiving a Critical Hit.",
  "1214": "Network Navigator +{0:#,#%} to Jumping and Summoning Cost Efficiency Snarky Genius -{2:#,#%} to opponent's Armor Piercing when defending from a player",
  "1215": "Network Navigator +{0:#,#%} to Jumping and Summoning Cost Efficiency Snarky Genius -{2:#,#%} to opponent's Armor Piercing when defending from a player",
  "1216": "CLASS: ENGINEERING GROUP: DISCOVERY CREW FACTION: FEDERATION When, in generations to come, students at Starfleet Academy study the brightest minds in Federation history, one name will stand out from all others; Paul Stamets. A genius in every sense of the word, Stamets rose through the ranks of Starfleet based on his masteries of biology, physics and quantum mechanics. He, along with a beloved friend, created technologies that would propel Starfleet to even greater heights, but none more so than his patented Spore Drive. When the war started, this marvelous technology was co-opted by Starfleet and pressed into service against the Klingons. Stamets loathed the idea of his creation being mishandled by incompetent warmongers and so insisted on managing the technology himself. Since then, he has seen the Discovery through countless unwinnable battles and treacherous situations, always counting on his brilliant mind to carry them to victory.",
  "1217": "Paul Stamets",
  "1218": "PAUL STAMETS",
  "1219": "Snarky Genius When defending against a Player, Stamets decreases the opponent's Armor Piercing by {0:0.#%}. Officer Abilities are activated when assigned to the bridge of a ship.",
  "1220": "Snarky Genius",
  "1221": "-{0:#,#%} to opponent's Armor Piercing when defending from a player",
  "1222": "Network Navigator Stamets increases the Cost Efficiency of Jumping and Summoning with the Discovery by {0:0.#%}. Captain Maneuvers are activated when an officer is captain of a ship.",
  "1223": "Network Navigator",
  "1224": "+{0:#,#%} to Jumping and Summoning Cost Efficiency",
  "1225": "Never Fire First -{0:#,#%} to opponent's Officer Attack when the opponent's ship is Burning Deceptive Warfare {3:#,#%} chance to deal Burning for two rounds at the start of each round",
  "1226": "Never Fire First -{0:#,#%} to opponent's Officer Attack when the opponent's ship is Burning Deceptive Warfare {3:#,#%} chance to deal Burning for two rounds at the start of each round",
  "1227": "CLASS: COMMAND GROUP: DISCOVERY FACTION: FEDERATION Despite a life filled with great loss, Philippa Georgiou never lost her hope for a brighter future. A true idealist, Georgiou sought to find the best in everyone. Her stalwart leadership, bright outlook and fierce determination made her a respected captain and a beloved friend. She was also not one to let rules stop her from making the right decisions. She arguably went against General Order One when she allowed Saru, a member of a pre-warp civilization, to join Starfleet. However, despite this, she was well respected by both her subordinates and superiors. Everyone knew that, when the chips were down, you could count on having Philippa Georgiou by your side.",
  "1228": "Georgiou",
  "1229": "GEORGIOU",
  "1230": "Deceptive Warfare At the beginning of each round, Georgiou has a {0:0.#%} chance of Burning the opponent's ship for 2 rounds. Officer Abilities are activated when assigned to the bridge of a ship.",
  "1231": "Deceptive Warfare",
  "1232": "{0:#.#%} chance to deal Burning for two rounds at the start of each round",
  "1233": "Never Fire First At the start of each round, if the opponent is Burning , Captain Georgiou decreases the Attack of all Officers on the opponent's ship by {0:0.#%} for that round. Decreasing Attack may result in a decrease in Damage Captain Maneuvers are activated when an officer is captain of a ship.",
  "1234": "Never Fire First",
  "1235": "-{0:#,#%} to opponent's Officer Attack when the opponent's ship is Burning",
  "1236": "The Power of Math -{0:#,#%} to opponent's Shield Health when defending from a player Hold Your Horses! {3:#,#%} chance to decrease opponent's Officer Attack by 15% when hit",
  "1237": "The Power of Math -{0:#,#%} to opponent's Shield Health when defending from a player Hold Your Horses! {3:#,#%} chance to decrease opponent's Officer Attack by 15% when hit",
  "1238": "CLASS: ENGINEERING GROUP: DISCOVERY FACTION: FEDERATION Don’t let her awkward demeanour fool you, Sylvia Tilly is an engineering prodigy. Tilly rated herself the greatest theoretical engineer in Starfleet academy. She was so impressive, in fact, that she was fast-tracked to serve on the USS Discovery, a science vessel built to test experimental warp technology. Tilly had always dreamed of becoming a captain, but feared that her social anxiety would hold her back. However, with the help of her good friend, Michael Burnham, she excelled in her training and was quickly promoted to the rank of Ensign by the time the Klingon war had ended. Tilly is motivated, compassionate and thoroughly dedicated to the ideals of Starfleet. There is no doubt in the mind of anyone who has served with her that she would make a remarkable captain.",
  "1239": "Tilly",
  "1240": "TILLY",
  "1241": "Hold Your Horses! Every time the ship is hit by an opponent's weapon attack, Tilly has a {0:0.#%} chance to decrease the opponent's officers Attack by 15% (cumulative) Decreasing Attack may result in a decrease in Damage Officer Abilities are activated when assigned to the bridge of a ship.",
  "1242": "Hold Your Horses!",
  "1243": "{1:#,#%} chance to decrease opponent's Officer Attack by 15% when hit",
  "1244": "The Power of Math At the start of combat, when defending from a player attack, Tilly decreases the opponent's Shield Health by {0:0.#%} of its starting Shield Health. Captain Maneuvers are activated when an officer is captain of a ship.",
