  "1524": "Headlong Into Battle +{0:#,#%} to Warp Speed after winning a battle (not cumulative) Only Fools Have No Fear +{2:#,#%} to all Mitigation against non-player targets",
  "1525": "Headlong Into Battle +{0:#,#%} to Warp Speed after winning a battle (not cumulative) Only Fools Have No Fear +{2:#,#%} to all Mitigation against non-player targets",
  "1526": "CLASS: COMMAND GROUP: TNG CREW FACTION: FEDERATION Fearless warrior. A man of two worlds. Worf, son of Mogh, is a Klingon warrior and Starfleet officer. At a young age, Worf lived on the Khitomer colony, which was eventually attacked by Romulan forces, leaving him orphaned. Luckily, he was rescued by a Federation vessel, the USS Intrepid, where he was adopted by the Rozhenko family. Worf grew up surrounded by humans, but kept close ties to his ancestral home. As the first of his kind to ever serve in Starfleet, he has constantly faced ridicule and rejection from fellow Klingons. Worf fights twice as hard for his honor, and has become a battle-sharpened edge as a result. Worf’s place as Chief Security aboard the Enterprise came after a stint as conn officer. He regularly reports to away team duty as the front line of defense for the landing party. Worf is a fearless and formidable warrior, with a bat’leth, or helming the tactical controls of a starship.",
  "1527": "Worf",
  "1528": "WORF",
  "1529": "Only Fools Have No Fear Worf increases all Mitigation stats against non-player targets by {0:0.#%}. Officer Abilities are activated when assigned to the bridge of a ship.",
  "1530": "Only Fools Have No Fear",
  "1531": "+{0:#,#%} to all Mitigation against non-player targets",
  "1532": "Headlong Into Battle After winning a battle, Worf increases the Warp Speed of the ship by {0:0.#%}. This bonus does not stack, and is removed when returning to your station. Captain Maneuvers are activated when an officer is captain of a ship.",
  "1533": "Headlong Into Battle",
  "1534": "+{0:#,#%} to Warp Speed after winning a battle",
  "1535": "Security Officer -{0:#,#%} to Crit Chance for Mission Hostiles (yellow hostiles) Code of Honor +{2:#,#%} to Damage against non-player targets",
  "1536": "Security Officer -{0:#,#%} to Crit Chance for Mission Hostiles (yellow hostiles) Code of Honor +{2:#,#%} to Damage against non-player targets",
  "1537": "CLASS: ENGINEERING GROUP: TNG CREW FACTION: FEDERATION Natasha Yar has her beginnings on the failed Federation colony Turkana IV, where she was born in 2337. Orphaned at a young age, she spent her early years fighting for survival and eking out an existence for herself and her sister. Tasha managed to escape Turkana IV in 2352 and joined Starfleet soon after. The lawlessness of Tasha’s harsh beginnings were her inspiration for becoming a Starfleet security officer, and her bravery and warrior’s soul allowed her to flourish in the role. Tasha’s mastery of martial arts and hand-to-hand combat make her a formidable opponent and a valued chief of security on the USS Enterprise-D. In her free time, Tasha likes to hone her aikido skills on the holodeck and participate in martial-arts and parrises squares tournaments with other members of the Enterprise crew.",
  "1538": "Tasha Yar",
  "1539": "TASHA YAR",
  "1540": "Code of Honor Tasha Yar increases all Weapon Damage against non-player targets by {0:0.#%}. Officer Abilities are activated when assigned to the bridge of a ship.",
  "1541": "Code of Honor",
