  "1578": "Increase Crit Damage by {0:#,#%} while cloaked",
  "1579": "Patient Tactician While cloaked, increase Armor Piercing, Shield Penetration, and Accuracy by {0:0.#%}. Death Over Disgrace Increase Damage against Klingon targets by {2:0.#%} of total Crew Attack.",
  "1580": "Patient Tactician While cloaked, increase Armor Piercing, Shield Penetration, and Accuracy by {0:0.#%}. Death Over Disgrace Increase Damage against Klingon targets by {2:0.#%} of total Crew Attack.",
  "1581": "CLASS: COMMAND GROUP: PRIDE OF ROMULUS FACTION: ROMULAN Tomalak is a Commander of the Romulan Military, and a master in surveillance, espionage, and intelligence. His affinity for deception has placed him at the forefront of Romulan operations into enemy territory, and he has played a significant role in ensuring that the Klingon Empire and Federation remain opposed. Tomalak’s preferred method of warfare is to lure enemies into traps, and to frame others for acts of atrocity that were carefully orchestrated to destroy their reputation. He believes strongly in tearing his rivals and enemies apart from within, rather than launching an all out attack. As a key military mind for the Senate, Tomalak is a powerful influence on the direction of Romulan tactics and strategy.",
  "1582": "Tomalak",
  "1583": "TOMALAK",
  "1584": "Death Over Disgrace Tomalak increases Weapon Damage against Klingon targets by {0:0.#%} of total Crew Attack. Officer Abilities are activated when assigned to the bridge of a ship.",
  "1585": "Death Over Disgrace",
  "1586": "Increase Damage against Klingons by {0:#,#%} of Crew Attack",
  "1587": "Patient Tactician While cloaked, Tomalak increases Armor Piercing, Shield Penetration, and Accuracy by {0:0.#%}. Captain Maneuvers are activated when an officer is captain of a ship.",
  "1588": "Patient Tactician",
  "1589": "Increase all Penetration stats by {0:#,#%} while cloaked",
  "1590": "Glorious Gaze +{0:#,#%} to Energy Weapon Damage Wartime Chancellor +{2:#,#%} of Crew Health to Shield Deflection",
  "1591": "Glorious Gaze +{0:#,#%} to Energy Weapon Damage Wartime Chancellor +{2:#,#%} of Crew Health to Shield Deflection",
  "1592": "CLASS: SCIENCE GROUP: KHITOMER'S REVENGE FACTION: KLINGON In order to dominate their enemies and claim eventual victory on the battlefield, a Klingon cannot solely rely on physical armaments such as the Bat’leth and Mek’leth. They must also possess the resolve to obtain glory for the Klingon Empire in the face of adversity. They must seek to eradicate those whose command would undermine the Empire’s prosperity. Gowron, son of M’Rel, was a living embodiment of this philosophy. Regarded as somewhat of an outsider in his early life, Gowron would often scrutinize the methods and actions of the Klingon High Council, challenging their decision-making and military strategies. His refusal to stand by and allow ineptitude to fester among the halls of the Council would eventually see Gowron take up the seat as the empire’s Chancellor. Although he may not have harbored aspirations of political leadership in his youth, Gowron quickly proved to be an efficient and pragmatic politician in his newfound calling. However, the heart and combat prowess of a warrior would always remain within him.",
  "1593": "Gowron",
  "1594": "GOWRON",
  "1595": "Wartime Chancellor Gowron increases the ship's Shield Deflection by {0:0.#%} of total Crew Health. Officer Abilities are activated when assigned to the bridge of a ship.",
  "1596": "Wartime Chancellor",
  "1597": "+{0:#,#%} of Crew Health to Shield Deflection",
  "1598": "Glorious Gaze Gowron increases the ship's Energy Weapon Damage by {0:0.#%}. Captain Maneuvers are activated when an officer is captain of a ship.",
  "1599": "Glorious Gaze",
  "1600": "+{0:#,#%} to Energy Weapon Damage",
  "1601": "Supreme Commander +{0:#,#%} to Kinetic Weapon Damage Wartime Chancellor +{2:#,#%} of Crew Defense to Dodge",
  "1602": "Supreme Commander +{0:#,#%} to Kinetic Weapon Damage Wartime Chancellor +{2:#,#%} of Crew Defense to Dodge",
  "1603": "CLASS: ENGINEERING GROUP: KHITOMER'S REVENGE FACTION: KLINGON General Martok is a loyal warrior of the Klingon Empire and a self-made man. Born into a common family in the Ketha Province on Kronos, Martok's ambition was to be an officer for the Klingon Defense Force. He was denied this honor due to his lack of noble blood, leaving him no option but to work as a civilian laborer aboard a battleship. However, during a battle with a Romulan ship, Martok fought with bravery and honor, and earned himself a commision as an officer. Over the course of the Klingon Civil War, Martok steadily gained influence and rank until he was awarded a general commission. He is known to be just, honorable and courageous, and is one of the most respected men within the Klingon Empire.",
  "1604": "Martok",
  "1605": "MARTOK",
  "1606": "Unwavering Loyalty Martok increases the ship's Dodge by {0:0.#%} of total Crew Defense. Officer Abilities are activated when assigned to the bridge of a ship.",
  "1607": "Unwavering Loyalty",
  "1608": "+{0:#,#%} of Crew Defense to Dodge",
  "1609": "Supreme Commander Martok increases the ship's Kinetic Weapon Damage by {0:0.#%}. Captain Maneuvers are activated when an officer is captain of a ship.",
  "1610": "Supreme Commander",
  "1611": "+{0:#,#%} to Kinetic Weapon Damage",
  "1612": "What's Mine Is Mine +{0:0.#%} to Protected Cargo of this ship Fight or Flight +{2:#,#%} to Warp Range of this ship",
  "1613": "What's Mine Is Mine +{0:0.#%} to Protected Cargo of this ship Fight or Flight +{2:#,#%} to Warp Range of this ship",
  "1614": "CLASS: COMMAND GROUP: SYNDICATE FACTION: NONE The Orion Syndicate was built as an organized crime unit that specialized in piracy, smuggling, slave-trading, and assassination. Over the years, the Syndicate has become the true power on Orion Prime and has dealings far and wide across the quadrant. As a trusted recruiter and Agent for the Syndicate, Ghrush is responsible for finding and manipulating those reckless enough to want a stake in the underworld’s high-risk rewards. Ghrush is a diligent and methodical operative. What he lacks in subtlety, he makes up for in reactionary tactical thinking. Having gotten himself into more than a few difficult situations, he has learned to trust his instincts. Fight or flight has become his motto, and Ghrush values his life more than one single payday. He’d much rather risk the lives of initiates than put himself in danger, and as a public face for the Syndicate, he has plenty of opportunity for profit.",
  "1615": "Ghrush",
  "1616": "GHRUSH",
  "1617": "Fight or Flight Ghrush increases the Warp Range of the ship by {0:0.#%}. Officer Abilities are activated when assigned to the bridge of a ship.",
  "1618": "Fight or Flight",
  "1619": "+{0:#,#%} to Warp Range",
  "1620": "What's Mine Is Mine Ghrush increases the Protected Cargo of the ship by {0:0.#%}. Captain Maneuvers are activated when an officer is captain of a ship.",
  "1621": "What's Mine Is Mine",
  "1622": "+{0:0.#%} to Protected Cargo",
  "1623": "Klingon Valor +{0:#,#%} to Weapon Damage Romulan Tact +{2:#,#%} of Crew Attack to Armor",
  "1624": "Klingon Valor +{0:#,#%} to Weapon Damage Romulan Tact +{2:#,#%} of Crew Attack to Armor",
  "1625": "CLASS: ENGINEERING GROUP: KHITOMER'S REVENGE FACTION: KLINGON Home is a difficult concept for those who live in two worlds. Ba’el is the daughter of a Romulan and a Klingon, a living contrast who never knew the reality of life outside of her peaceful commune. She was content to live a simple, quiet life with her family and friends, far from the worries of the galaxy. That was, until she met Worf. Ba’el immediately fell in love with this strange Starfleet officer, though it was not fully reciprocated. Even when her family turned on him, when her people were ready to kill him, she stood by his side. It was thanks to her that Worf made it back to the Enterprise in one piece. Loyal, determined and with a will of iron, Ba’el shows the best qualities of both Romulans and Klingons.",
  "1626": "Ba'el",
  "1627": "BA'EL",
