  "2532": "Chain of Command",
  "2533": "No effect.",
  "2534": "Andorian Mining Consortium Shran increases Crystal mining speed by {0:0.#%} ({1:#,#%} at rank {2:#,#}) of base. Below-Decks Abilities are only activated when assigned to a below-decks slot on a ship.",
  "2535": "Andorian Mining Consortium",
  "2536": "Shran increases Crystal mining speed by {0:#,#%} of base.",
  "2537": "Chain of Command This Captain's Maneuver has no effect. Plan For The Future Increase the amount of raw Ore, Crystal and Gas collected while mining with any ship by an extra {2:#,#%}, without draining the mining node faster. Reclaiming Lives At the beginning of each round of combat Hugh repairs {4:#,#%} of hull damage taken in the previous round of combat.",
  "2538": "Chain of Command This Captain's Maneuver has no effect. Plan For The Future Increase the amount of raw Ore, Crystal and Gas collected while mining with any ship by an extra {2:#,#%}, without draining the mining node faster. Reclaiming Lives At the beginning of each round of combat Hugh repairs {4:#,#%} of hull damage taken in the previous round of combat.",
  "2539": "CLASS: ENGINEERING GROUP: EX-BORG FACTION: EX-BORG Life as a Borg drone is long gone for Hugh, but his scars will never heal. Losing a connection to the Collective is not an easy feat. While some manage to recover from this experience, for others, this process and the resulting struggles will hardly ever end. Knowing just how challenging reclaiming one's own life could be, it's no wonder that Hugh, one of the first drones to gain self-consciousness, received the executive director position of the Borg Reclamation Project. With his help, numerous Ex-Borgs gained hope and found support in a world where their kind is treated like hazardous waste or an inanimate workforce. If there were one word to describe Hugh, it would be loyalty: loyalty to the cause and his friends. During his work at the Borg Reclamation Project, he stood by his fellow Ex-Borgs, protecting them from the opportunistic and ruthless Romulans, and by Captain Picard when he required help in saving the universe once again. Such selflessness doesn't always end well, but in Hugh's case, it means no Ex-Borg will be left behind, and as long as his kind has hopes of a better tomorrow, he will keep fighting for it.",
  "2540": "PIC Hugh",
  "2541": "PIC HUGH",
  "2542": "Plan For The Future Increase the amount of raw Ore, Crystal and Gas collected while mining with any ship by an extra {0:#.#%} ({1:#,#%} at rank {2:#,#}), without draining the mining node faster. Officer Abilities are activated when assigned to the bridge of a ship.",
  "2543": "Plan For The Future",
  "2544": "Increase the amount of raw Ore, Crystal or Gas mined by an extra {0:#.#%}, without draining the mining node faster.",
