  "2565": "Chain of Command This Captain's Maneuver has no effect. Denobulan Threat Response On combat start against players and Hostiles, Phlox reduces the opponent's Critical Hit Chance by {2:#,#%} , for 8 rounds. (Does not trigger at Armadas, Assaults or Station Combat). Specimen Cataloguing Phlox increases the efficiency of charging the Borg Cube's Cutting Beam by {4:#,#%}",
  "2566": "Chain of Command This Captain's Maneuver has no effect. Denobulan Threat Response On combat start against players and Hostiles, Phlox reduces the opponent's Critical Hit Chance by {2:#,#%} , for 8 rounds. (Does not trigger at Armadas, Assaults, or Station Combat). Specimen Cataloguing Phlox increases the efficiency of charging the Borg Cube's Cutting Beam by {4:#,#%}",
  "2567": "CLASS: SCIENCE GROUP: ENTERPRISE NX-01 FACTION: FEDERATION One of the first aliens to serve aboard the Enterprise, Doctor Phlox of Denobula is one of its most beloved, most valuable crew members. Despite having only six months of service within Starfleet, the good Doctor Phlox was selected to assist the Enterprise in her maiden voyage following a miraculous treatment of a dying Klingon warrior. Although his patient would eventually be captured by the Suliban, Phlox continued to serve with distinction aboard the Enterprise, proving himself an invaluable member of the crew on numerous occasions. Even considering his odd propensity of collecting and cataloging odd alien fauna, one could not ask for a better physician, especially if one’s life is on the line.",
  "2568": "Phlox",
  "2569": "PHLOX",
  "2570": "Denobulan Threat Response On combat start against players and hostiles, Phlox reduces the opponent's Critical Hit Chance by {0:#,#%} ({1:#,#%} at rank {2:#,#}), for 8 rounds. (Does not trigger at Armadas, Assaults or Station Combat). Officer Abilities are activated when assigned to the bridge of a ship.",
