  "2703": "Test That Assumption Lieutenant Picard increases your Apex Barrier by {0:#} vs non-Armada hostiles.Apex Barrier provides true damage mitigation from all sources after all other bonuses. Every 100 Apex Barrier increases the damage you can take by 1%. With full Synergy, Lieutenant Picard provides 11,000 Apex Barrier which reduces the incoming damage by 55%. Works against Hostiles of level 35 and under. This ability does not trigger when Tal is assigned to the bridge of your ship. Captain Maneuvers are activated when an officer is captain of a ship.",
  "2704": "Test That Assumption",
  "2705": "Lieutenant Picard increases your Apex Barrier by {0:#} vs non-Armada hostiles. Apex Barrier provides true damage mitigation from all sources after all other bonuses. Every 100 Apex Barrier increases the damage you can take by 1%. With full Synergy, Lieutenant Picard provides 11,000 Apex Barrier which reduces the incoming damage by 55%. Works against Hostiles of level 35 and under. This ability does not trigger when Tal is assigned to the bridge of your ship. Captain Maneuvers are activated when an officer is captain of a ship.",
  "2706": "Never Give Up Decreases Invading Entities Shield Mitigation by {0:0.#%} Never Surrender Increases your Apex Barrier by {2:#,#%} when fighting hostiles.",
  "2707": "Never Give Up Decreases Invading Entities Shield Mitigation by {0:0.#%} Never Surrender Increases your Apex Barrier by {2:#,#} when fighting hostiles.",
  "2708": "CLASS: COMMAND GROUP: NSEA PROTECTOR FACTION: INDEPENDENT Some are destined to walk an unbeaten path, fated to change the course of history forever. Some men are simply born to be heroes. Jason Nesmith is not one of those men. Making a name for himself as Peter Quincy Taggart in the cult classic television series, Galaxy Quest, Nesmith found himself quite comfortable in the role, never quite pushing his boundaries, never questioning whether or not he could have a greater career elsewhere. When the show was canceled after a particularly nail-biting cliffhanger, most of the cast were relieved to finally be free of it. Nesmith, however, never quite recovered from the sting of losing his golden goose. In the years to come, the aging actor held on to whatever scraps of relevancy he could, appearing at conventions, store-openings, and in more than a few car insurance commercials. However, as his career appeared to hit rock bottom, Nesmith found himself catapulted into a real space adventure. Along with his former castmates, Jason captained the Protector in a battle against the fierce dictator, Sarris. Thanks to his ingenuity, wit, and a good dash of dumb luck, Nesmith managed to defeat the tyrant and save the day. With his confidence restored and his relationship with his crew stronger, Nesmith returned to his role as Commander Taggart in a revitalized Galaxy Quest TV series that promised to be better than ever before...",
  "2709": "Jason Nesmith",
  "2710": "NESMITH",
  "2711": "Never Surrender Jason Nesmith increases your Apex Barrier by {0:#} ({1:#} at rank {2:#,#}) when fighting hostiles. Apex Barrier provides true damage mitigation from all sources after all other bonuses. Every 100 Apex Barrier increases the damage you can take by 1%. This ability does not trigger when Tal is assigned to the bridge of your ship. Officer Abilities are activated when assigned to the bridge of a ship.",
  "2712": "Never Surrender",
  "2713": "Increases your Apex Barrier by {0:#} when fighting hostiles",
  "2714": "Never Give Up Jason Nesmith decreases Invading Entities Shield Mitigation by {0:0.#%} Captain Maneuvers are activated when an officer is captain of a ship.",
  "2715": "Never Give Up",
  "2716": "Decreases Invading Entities Shield Mitigation by {0:0.#%}",
  "2717": "Chain of Command This Captain's Maneuver has no effect. I Have One Job! Gwen DeMarco increases Isolytic Cascade damage against Armadas and Invading Entities by {2:0.#%} Hold, Please Gwen DeMarco Increases Isolytic Cascade damage in PvP when the enemy player has any state by {4:0.#%}",
  "2718": "Chain of Command This Captain's Maneuver has no effect. I Have One Job! Gwen DeMarco increases Isolytic Cascade damage against Armadas and Invading Entities by {2:0.#%} Hold, Please Gwen DeMarco Increases Isolytic Cascade damage in PvP when the enemy player has any state by {4:0.#%}",
  "2719": "CLASS: SCIENCE GROUP: NSEA PROTECTOR FACTION: INDEPENDENT The term “unsung hero” is thrown around a lot in Hollywood. However, nobody is more deserving of that moniker than Gwen DeMarco. Possibly the most enthusiastic member of the original Galaxy Quest cast, Gwen had thrown everything behind the character of Lieutenant Tawny Madison. Despite her character being horribly mismanaged by the misogynistic writers of the time, Gwen never let it stop her from being the best version of herself she could be. She truly lived by the old saying, “no role is too small.” Unlike most of the other cast members, Gwen would go on to maintain a fantastic relationship with the fans of the show. Where her cast-mates mocked the enthusiastic, die-hard viewers, or otherwise viewed them as little more than cash-cows, Gwen went out of her way to treat the fans with kindness and gratitude, aware that her career was built on their devotion. During the Protector crew’s ill-fated space adventure, DeMarco proved to be a sharp, quick-witted bridge officer, throwing herself into life-threatening situations to save her friends. Along with Nesmith, she was able to brave the Chompers and activate the Omega-13 device, bringing about Sarris’ destruction.",
  "2720": "Gwen DeMarco",
  "2721": "DEMARCO",
  "2722": "I Have One Job! Gwen DeMarco increases Isolytic Cascade damage against Armadas and Invading Entities by {0:0.#%} ({1:#,#%} at rank {2:#,#}) Isolytic Cascade multiplies your total damage, including Isolytic Damage, and all research and other bonuses. Officer Abilities are activated when assigned to the bridge of a ship.",
  "2723": "I Have One Job!",
