  "2844": "Increases base protected cargo by {0:0.#%}",
  "2845": "Chain of Command This Captain's Maneuver has no effect. Master Manipulator Increases your existing Apex Barrier by {2:#,#%} for 2 rounds after receiving HHP damage from a player ship with Assimilate . Silent Partner Increases your Apex Barrier by {4:#,#} at the start of combat versus non-Armada Hostiles.",
  "2846": "Chain of Command This Captain's Maneuver has no effect. Master Manipulator Increases your existing Apex Barrier by {2:#,#} for 2 rounds after receiving HHP damage from a player ship with Assimilate . Silent Partner Increases your Apex Barrier by {4:#,#} at the start of combat versus non-Armada Hostiles.",
  "2847": "CLASS: SCIENCE GROUP: MIRROR UNIVERSE FACTION: TERRAN EMPIRE Rightful Empress of Terra? Perhaps. Master manipulator? Certainly. Nyota Uhura is as vengeful and power-hungry as the most ruthless of Terrans, though she is adept at hiding her sharp teeth behind a sweet smile. Like her Kelvin counterpart, she serves as a communications officer on the ISS Enterprise. But that is where the similarities end. Uhura believes in taking what she wants when she wants it. She does not, however, believe in gratuitous violence. She prefers to wield her power quietly. There is no need for daggers when she can simply blackmail those who stand against her. It is perhaps surprising, then, that Uhura has invested in the Arena; she would never lower herself to actually participate in the gladiatorial games. Why should she get her hands dirty battling with and against the masses? Instead, she is a silent partner in this burgeoning enterprise. It is a solid investment, after all, and what better way to keep track of the most powerful warriors in her own universe and beyond? There are alliances to be made and secrets to be found out. And Nyota Uhura is the perfect woman for the job.",
  "2848": "Mirror Uhura",
  "2849": "MIRROR UHURA",
  "2850": "Master Manipulator Increases your existing Apex Barrier by {0:#,#%} ({1:#,#%} at rank {2:#,#}) for 2 rounds after receiving HHP damage from a player ship with Assimilate (Once per weapon). This ability does not trigger when Tal is assigned to the bridge of your ship or during station combat. Apex Barrier provides true damage mitigation from all sources after all other bonuses. Every 100 Apex Barrier increases the damage you can take by 1%. Officer Abilities are activated when assigned to the bridge of a ship.",
  "2851": "Master Manipulator",
  "2852": "+{0:#,#%} to existing Apex Barrier when you are hit by a player with Assimilate.",
  "2853": "Chain of Command This Officer does not have a Captain's Maneuver. Equipping this Officer as the captain of a ship provides no benefit.",
  "2854": "Chain of Command",
  "2855": "No effect.",
  "2856": "Silent Partner Increases your Apex Barrier by {0:#,#} ({1:#,#} at rank {2:#,#}) at the start of combat versus non-Armada Hostiles. This ability does not trigger when Tal is assigned to the bridge of your ship. Apex Barrier provides true damage mitigation from all sources after all other bonuses. Every 100 Apex Barrier increases the damage you can take by 1%. Below-Decks Abilities are only activated when assigned to a below-decks slot on a ship.",
  "2857": "Silent Partner",
  "2858": "+{0:#,#} to Apex Barrier at the start of combat against non-Armada Hostiles.",
  "2859": "Mon Capitaine On round start against players, Starfleet Q has {1:#,#%} chance to apply Morale to your ship for 1 round. You Hit Me! On round start, if placed on a ship with Morale against players commanding an Interceptor, Starfleet Q increases your Apex Barrier by {2:#} for 5 rounds. Apex Barrier provides true damage mitigation from all sources after all other bonuses. Every 100 Apex Barrier increases the damage you can take by 1%.",
  "2860": "Mon Capitaine On round start against players, Starfleet Q has {1:#,#%} chance to apply Morale to your ship for 1 round. You Hit Me! On round start, if placed on a ship with Morale against players commanding an Interceptor, Starfleet Q increases your Apex Barrier by {2:#} for 5 rounds. Apex Barrier provides true damage mitigation from all sources after all other bonuses. Every 100 Apex Barrier increases the damage you can take by 1%.",
  "2861": "CLASS: COMMAND GROUP: INTERCEPTOR RETALIATION SQUAD FACTION: Q In the year 2364, under the command of Captain Jean-Luc Picard, the USS Enterprise-D embarked on its maiden voyage to Deneb IV. Its mission was to make contact with a species known as the Bandi and investigate the expedited construction of Farpoint Station. However, en route to Deneb IV, Captain Picard and his crew would encounter a being unlike any other - the omnipotent Q. Hailing from an extra-dimensional realm known as the Q Continuum, Q took it upon himself to place humanity as a whole on trial for alleged savagery and barbarism throughout their history. While Captain Picard was successful in his defense of humanity's history and standing among their galactic peers, Q would find himself personally fascinated with Picard, and the two would go on to develop a complicated and storied relationship with one another. Over the subsequent years, Q would continue to appear without notice to unsuspecting Starfleet crews and captains, ready to test their moral ethics and question humanity's place in the galaxy. While capable of adopting any external appearance that he saw fit, Q would frequently apparate on the bridge of a Starfleet vessel in the form of a male humanoid donned in full captain's uniform. Although his motivations for doing so were questionable, and could be easily mistaken for stolen valor, this mockery was nothing more than an attempt to unsettle the Starfleet captain unfortunate enough to find Q on their bridge.",
  "2862": "Starfleet Q",
  "2863": "STARFLEET Q",
  "2864": "You Hit Me! On round start, if placed on a ship with Morale against players commanding an Interceptor, Starfleet Q increases your Apex Barrier by {0:0,#} ({1:#,#} at rank {2:#,#}) for 5 rounds. This ability does not trigger when Tal is assigned to the bridge of your ship. Apex Barrier provides true damage mitigation from all sources after all other bonuses. Every 100 Apex Barrier increases the damage you can take by 1%. Officer Abilities are activated when assigned to the bridge of a ship.",
  "2865": "You Hit Me!",
  "2866": "On round start, if on a ship with Morale against players commanding an Interceptor, increase your Apex Barrier by {0:#} for 5 rounds.",
