  "2910": "Chain of Command This Captain's Maneuver has no effect. Flaming Shots On round start against players afflicted by Burning, Romi increases your Isolytic Defense by {2:#,#%} for 3 rounds. Active Listening On round start against players afflicted by Hull Breach, Romi increases your Apex Barrier by {4:#,#} for 1 round.",
  "2911": "CLASS: SCIENCE GROUP: EXPLORER RETALIATION SQUAD FACTION: INDEPENDENT In the 23rd century, the Borg Collective invaded the El-Aurian homeworld. The assimilation of the El-Aurians was swift and brutal, with their culture and way of life decimated in mere moments. As millions of El-Aurians were either assimilated or killed, a small number of survivors were scattered to the stars. Following their escape from the Borg, a contingent of 415 El-Aurian refugees were traveling to Earth when their transport vessels, the SS Lakul and SS Robert Fox, became trapped in a powerful and erratic energy ribbon which acted as a doorway to an extra-dimensional realm known as the Nexus. With the destruction of the transport ships by the forces of the energy ribbon deemed an inevitability, the USS Enterprise-B launched a rescue mission, managing to rescue 47 El-Aurian refugees in the process. Romi was one of those survivors.",
