  "2960": "Purity of Will",
  "2961": "On round start against players, if on a ship with no State applied increases your Isolytic Cascade damage by {0:0.#%} for 3 rounds (Cumulative).",
  "2962": "Chain of Command This Captain's Maneuver has no effect. Vulcan Security Procedures Against players with Hull Breach, Infiltrator Tuvok increases your increases your Isolytic Cascade damage by {2:0,#%} for 3 rounds each time you score a hit (Once per weapon)(Cumulative). Logical Tactics On round start against players, if on a ship with no State applied Infiltrator Tuvok increases your Apex Barrier by {4:#} for 3 rounds (Cumulative).",
  "2963": "Chain of Command This Captain's Maneuver has no effect. Vulcan Security Procedures Against players with Hull Breach, Infiltrator Tuvok increases your increases your Isolytic Cascade damage by {2:0,#%} for 3 rounds each time you score a hit (Once per weapon)(Cumulative). Logical Tactics On round start against players, if on a ship with no State applied Infiltrator Tuvok increases your Apex Barrier by {4:#} for 3 rounds (Cumulative).",
  "2964": "CLASS: SCIENCE GROUP: BATTLESHIP RETALIATION SQUAD FACTION: FEDERATION After returning to Earth, Tuvok, along with the rest of the crew of Voyager, were given a hero’s welcome. Tuvok was promoted to Commander and rewarded with a comfortable posting at Starfleet Academy, utilizing his vast experience in the Delta Quadrant to raise the next generation of explorers. However, something scratched at the back of Tuvok’s mind. Sentiment and emotion were, of course, human faults but even still, he felt... he felt. This creeping growth of emotion began to disturb Tuvok. He was becoming anxious, irritable. He was having dreams, nightmares of his assimilation by the Borg. Tuvok needed clarity. He needed Vulcan. Taking a temporary leave of absence, Tuvok bid a fond farewell to his friends and crewmates and set out once more to his home world of Vulcan. There, he hoped he would once again find peace in the comforting embrace of Logic.",
  "2965": "Infiltrator Tuvok",
  "2966": "INFILTRATOR TUVOK",
  "2967": "Vulcan Security Procedures Against players with Hull Breach, Infiltrator Tuvok increases your Isolytic Cascade damage by {0:0,#%} ({1:#,#%} at rank {2:#,#}) for 3 rounds each time you score a hit (Once per weapon)(Cumulative). Isolytic Cascade multiplies your total damage, including Isolytic Damage, and all research and other bonuses. Officer Abilities are activated when assigned to the bridge of a ship.",
  "2968": "Vulcan Security Procedures",
  "2969": "Against players with Hull Breach, increases your Isolytic Cascade damage by {0:0,#%} for 3 rounds each time you score a hit (Cumulative).",
  "2970": "This Officer does not have a Captain's Maneuver. Equipping this Officer as the captain of a ship provides no benefit.",
  "2971": "Chain of Command",
  "2972": "No effect.",
  "2973": "Logical Tactics On round start against players, if on a ship with no State applied Infiltrator Tuvok increases your Apex Barrier by {0:#} ({1:#,#} at rank {2:#,#}) for 3 rounds (Cumulative). Apex Barrier provides true damage mitigation from all sources after all other bonuses. Every 100 Apex Barrier increases the damage you can take by 1%. This ability does not trigger when Tal is assigned to the bridge of your ship. Below-Decks Abilities are only activated when assigned to a below-decks slot on a ship.",
  "2974": "Logical Tactics",
  "2975": "On round start against players, if on a ship with no State applied increases your Apex Barrier by {0:#} for 3 rounds (Cumulative).",
  "2976": "Past, Present, and Future Increases the rewards gained from Hostile Chests by {0:#,#%} of base. Time is Patient Increases Apex Barrier by {2:#,#%} for 2 rounds when hit by a hostile.",
  "2977": "Past, Present, and Future Increases the rewards gained from Hostile Chests by {0:#,#%} of base. Time is Patient Increases Apex Barrier by {2:#,#%} for 2 rounds when hit by a hostile.",
  "2978": "CLASS: COMMAND GROUP: VOYAGER 30TH ANNIVERSARY FACTION: INDEPENDENT If you could save your people from destruction while damning yourself in the process, would you do it? Annorax of the Krenim Imperium was a brilliant man. Intelligent, cunning, and fiercely devoted to his people. He pledged to stop at nothing to restore the Krenim to their rightful place as a dominant power in the galaxy. Desperate to protect his people from their age-old enemies, the Rinar, Annorax discovered a method of pushing elements out of the space-time continuum, thereby creating an alternate timeline where that element never existed. This science was weaponized immediately. In the years that followed, the Krenim became an unstoppable force in the Delta Quadrant. That is, until they were ultimately defeated by Kathryn Janeway and the crew of the USS Voyager. Driven by naught but an unquenchable desire for revenge against Janeway, Annorax has launched a full-scale temporal invasion of the Alpha Quadrant. This time, we may not have Janeway to save us...",
  "2979": "Annorax",
  "2980": "ANNORAX",
  "2981": "Time is Patient Increases Apex Barrier by {0:#} ({1:#} at rank {2:#,#}) for 2 rounds when hit by a hostile (Once per weapon)(Cumulative). Apex Barrier provides true damage mitigation from all sources after all other bonuses. Every 100 Apex Barrier increases the damage you can take by 1%. This ability does not trigger when Tal is assigned to the bridge of your ship. Officer Abilities are activated when assigned to the bridge of a ship.",
  "2982": "Time is Patient",
  "2983": "Increases Apex Barrier by {0:#} for 2 rounds when hit by a hostile.",
  "2984": "Past, Present, and Future Increases select rewards from hostile chests (G3-G6 Parts & Refined Materials, FKR Messages & Credits, Hirogen Relics, Mycellium, Exotic Biotoxins, Xindi Scraps & Bounties, Trellium, Fatu-Kray Scraps) by {0:0.#%} of base. Captain Maneuvers are activated when an officer is captain of a ship.",
  "2985": "Past, Present, and Future",
  "2986": "Increases the rewards gained from Hostile Chests by {0:0.#%} of base.",
  "2987": "Chain of Command This Captain's Maneuver has no effect. Lone Operative Restores the Shield Health of your ship every round by {2:#,#%} when fighting hostiles. Treacherous Ideals Increases Critical Hit Damage by {4:#,#%} for 4 rounds each time you score a hit (Once per weapon) when fighting hostiles.",
  "2988": "Chain of Command This Captain's Maneuver has no effect. Lone Operative Restores the Shield Health of your ship every round by {2:#,#%} when fighting hostiles. Treacherous Ideals Increases Critical Hit Damage by {4:#,#%} for 4 rounds each time you score a hit (Once per weapon) when fighting hostiles.",
  "2989": "CLASS: SCIENCE GROUP: VOYAGER 30TH ANNIVERSARY FACTION: INDEPENDENT How far would you go to save your own life? Trapped thousands of light years from home and faced with a future of endless wandering of the stars, Seska made a decision. She would do what no one else aboard Voyager had the courage to do. She would save her own life. Seska betrayed her fellow crew members, acting as a spy for the Cardassians under the promise of an imminent return to Earth. Of course, their promise of salvation was fictitious, but desperate people are willing to believe almost anything. Seska proved herself as a cunning, dedicated operative, successfully hiding her true intentions from her crew for some time before she was eventually exposed as a traitor.",
  "2990": "Seska",
  "2991": "SESKA",
  "2992": "Lone Operative Restores the Shield Health of your ship every round by {0:#,#%} ({1:#,#%} at rank {2:#,#}) when fighting hostiles. Officer Abilities are activated when assigned to the bridge of a ship.",
